						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 44: 1113-14 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This epigraph records an undertaking similar to the above, given by the <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇa</hi> Bhāradvāji Tirunīlakaṇṭhaṉ Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiyāṉ and his brother Kunikkum Pirāṉ to Uruvāṟu-kiḻāṉ Ēṟaṉ Tiruvālinambi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Na[ñ*]-chey[ya*]pādappichchaṉ to burn a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulavallinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu for 1(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> received from him.</p>						

						</summary>
